                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/9586</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-27T23:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1918, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 28, 7.27 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4604. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1"
                        >McFadden</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 300. Referring our No. 284 of July 20. For your information. The British
                    delegate on I. B. C., Paris, has received from his Government a telegram
                    requesting Japan’s participation in preparation of the black list pending
                    further communication from London. Arguments used at the meeting yesterday
                    against such participation in Paris were: First, if Japan were asked, it might
                    necessitate inviting representatives of other Associated Governments not now
                    represented, with the result of increasing size committee, complicating
                    discussions, and retarding decisions; second, Paris committee is not concerned
                    with question relative to Far East which your committee handles. <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
